description: Enforce red-green-refactor TDD workflow for all code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

# AI TDD Harness

- For every backend/frontend logic change, follow strict `red -> green -> refactor`.
- Start from a failing test first (red) using the smallest possible test scope.
- Implement only the minimal code needed to pass (green).
- Refactor only after tests pass, then rerun broad checks (refactor).
- Use harness commands:
  - `npm run harness:tdd:red` with `TDD_CMD` set to a failing test.
  - `npm run harness:tdd:green` with the same `TDD_CMD`.
  - `npm run harness:tdd:refactor` before finalizing.
- Do not skip red phase unless explicitly asked by the user.
- If no test exists yet, add a minimal targeted test before implementation.
